article.headline: New Mexico 75, New Mexico St. 58
article.story: ALBUQUERQUE, N.M. -- Roman Martinez scored 21 points to lead four New Mexico players in double figures, helping the Lobos remain undefeated with a 75-58 victory over New Mexico State on Saturday night. Martinez did most of his damage on 3-pointers, hitting 5 of 8 as New Mexico (8-0) swept the home-and-home season series. Darington Hobson added 14 points. Gordo Castillo led New Mexico State (2-5) with 17 points. Midway through the first half, the Lobos, who never trailed, went on a 22-5 run to expand their lead to 33-10. A.J. Hardeman's seven points and blocked shot fueled the run. New Mexico led by 26 points, 53-27, at the 15:35 mark of the second half before the Aggies rallied to within 67-58 with three minutes left.
